      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Validation — Five Operating Points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against measured plasma free hemoglobin (pfHb) concentrations collected during the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump hemolysis measurement campaign. Across all five flow-speed combinations, the CFD model predicted RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. The measurement data were gathered by trained laboratory personnel who monitored pump operating conditions, collected blood samples at standardized intervals, and recorded all relevant parameters including flow rate, rotational speed, and temperature. The study team characterised this campaign as a rigorous, prospective data-collection effort providing high-quality experimental grounding for CFD validation. Agreement between predicted and measured NIH values was within 12% across all operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute relative error 9.4%; RH < 1 at all five operating points",
